.TH "__clocksource_update_freq_scale" 9 "__clocksource_update_freq_scale" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__clocksource_update_freq_scale \- Used update clocksource with new freq
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __clocksource_update_freq_scale
.BI "(struct clocksource *cs "  ","
.BI "u32 scale "  ","
.BI "u32 freq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cs" 12
clocksource to be registered
.IP "scale" 12
Scale factor multiplied against freq to get clocksource hz
.IP "freq" 12
clocksource frequency (cycles per second) divided by scale
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This should only be called from the clocksource->\fBenable\fP method.

This *SHOULD NOT* be called directly! Please use the
\fB__clocksource_update_freq_hz\fP or \fB__clocksource_update_freq_khz\fP helper
functions.
